headline: Pro-Iran Hackers Post on U.S. Library Site
abstract: Officials were still investigating the attack, which was consistent with the work of low-level Iranian nationalist hackers looking for easy American targets, experts said.
lead_paragraph: A federal government website was hacked over the weekend to show messages vowing revenge for the death of Iranâ€™s most powerful commander and a doctored photograph of President Trump being punched in the jaw. The intrusion was consistent with the work of low-level nationalist Iranian hackers, experts said.
